    "body": "> Using `--private.api.addr=localhost:9090` I expected it to work in remote mode, but I'm getting a `Could not connect to DB`. when I set `--datadir /var/lib/erigon`.\r\n\r\nYour statement is a bit confusing to me.\r\nYou say you're expected to work in \"remote\" mode (aka socket mode) so why would you add --datadir ?\r\nThat cli option is only needed if you want rpcdaemon to speed up some queries by a direct access to db.\r\nThis said it appears to me you're trying to instantiate rpcdaemon from **a different** docker container than the one erigon is running into. This is highly discouraged due to how locking mechanisms are handled by PID in MDBX",
